事发后，尽管被告知太过危险，州长卡西姆·谢蒂马还是要求参观奇博克。4月21日，军方联合义务警员和志愿者，在尼日利亚和喀麦隆边境附近的森林展看搜索工作<ref name=USAToday/>。[[联合国秘书长|联合国秘书长]][[潘基文|潘基文]]、[[联合国儿童基金会|联合国儿童基金会]]<ref>{{cite press release|title=UN calls for immediate release of abducted school girls in north-eastern Nigeria|url=http://www.un.org/apps/news/story.asp?NewsID=47593|accessdate=2014-04-26|publisher=UN News Centre|archive-date=2014-04-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140424083958/http://www.un.org/apps/news/story.asp?NewsID=47593|dead-url=no}}</ref>与前尼日利亚军方统帅[[穆罕默杜·布哈里|穆罕默杜·布哈里]]谴责此次绑架<ref>{{cite news|last=Aziken|first=Emmanuel|title=Buhari to Boko Haram: You're bigots masquerading as Muslims|work=Vanguard News|accessdate=2014-05-09|date=2014-05-08|url=http://www.vanguardngr.com/2014/05/buhari-boko-haram-youre-bigots-masquerading-muslims/|archive-date=2014-05-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140509023342/http://www.vanguardngr.com/2014/05/buhari-boko-haram-youre-bigots-masquerading-muslims/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。[[联合国安理会|联合国安理会]]亦谴责此次袭击，并警告称要针对博科圣地武装分子绑架女孩采取行动<ref>{{cite web|title=UNSC warns action against Boko Haram Militants in Nigeria|url=http://news.biharprabha.com/2014/05/unsc-warns-action-against-boko-haram-militants-in-nigeria/|work=IANS|publisher=news.biharprabha.com|accessdate=2014-05-10|archive-date=2014-05-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140512040343/http://news.biharprabha.com/2014/05/unsc-warns-action-against-boko-haram-militants-in-nigeria/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

家长和其他人通过社交媒体抱怨政府感应缓慢，反应不充分。这一消息引发国际对博科圣地和尼日利亚政府的公愤。4月30日和5月1日，尼日利亚多个城市爆发示威，要求尼日利亚政府采取更多行动<ref name=VOA52>{{cite news|place=Nigeria|title=Authorities – 276 Kidnapped Girls Still Missing in Nigeria|work=VOA|publisher=All Africa|date=2014-05-02|url=http://allafrica.com/stories/201405021859.html|accessdate=2014-05-02|archive-date=2015-08-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150810054358/http://allafrica.com/stories/201405021859.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。然而，大多数家长害怕他们的女儿会遇到针对性的报复，不敢公开谈论。5月3日和4日，包括[[洛杉矶|洛杉矶]]和[[伦敦|伦敦]]等西方国家主要城市举行示威活动。尼日利亚首都[[阿布贾|阿布贾]]一名律师发起的[[主题标签|主题标签]]#BringBackOurGirls（带我们的女孩回来）登上[[Twitter|Twitter]]全球趋势榜，该报道在国际快速传播，一时间成为Twitter最多推文的话题<ref name="Lamb">{{cite news|last1=Lamb|first1=Christina|title=A fight for the soul of the world|url=http://www.thesundaytimes.co.uk/sto/public/magazine/article1680538.ece|accessdate=2016-03-23|publisher=Sunday Times|date=2016-03-20|archive-date=2016-11-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161129233128/http://www.thesundaytimes.co.uk/sto/public/magazine/article1680538.ece|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name = sell>{{cite news|last1=Abubakar|first1=Aminu|title='I will sell them,' Boko Haram leader says of kidnapped Nigerian girls|url=http://www.cnn.com/2014/05/05/world/africa/nigeria-abducted-girls/|accessdate=2014-05-05|agency=CNN|date=2014-05-05|first2=Josh|last2=Levs|archive-date=2014-05-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140505155919/http://www.cnn.com/2014/05/05/world/africa/nigeria-abducted-girls/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。5月11日，话题获得230万条推文<ref>Lamb, Cristina (11 May 2014) [http://www.thesundaytimes.co.uk/sto/news/article1409341.ece Find our girls and save their dreams] {{Wayback|url=http://www.thesundaytimes.co.uk/sto/news/article1409341.ece |date=20160404004928 }} The Times, (online version may need a subscription) Retrieved 12 May 2014</ref><ref>Collins, Matt (9 May 2014) [http://www.theguardian.com/voluntary-sector-network/2014/may/09/bringbackourgirls-power-of-social-media #BringBackOurGirls: the power of a social media campaign] {{Wayback|url=http://www.theguardian.com/voluntary-sector-network/2014/may/09/bringbackourgirls-power-of-social-media |date=20160812131336 }} The Guardian, Retrieved 11 May 2014</ref>，到2016年被转发610万次<ref name="Lamb"/>。一名协助组织抗议的女性被警方拘留，明显是因为{{le|尼日利亚第一夫人|First Lady of Nigeria}}{{le|裴纯丝·乔纳森|Patience Jonathan}}觉得女性代替受害者的母亲亮相会议是件轻蔑的事<ref name=BBC/><ref name="thepunch20140509">{{cite news |title=The Economist accuses Jonathan of incompetence |work=The Punch |accessdate=2014-05-09 |date=2014-05-10 |url=http://www.punchng.com/news/the-economist-accuses-jonathan-of-incompetence/ |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140510174232/http://www.punchng.com/news/the-economist-accuses-jonathan-of-incompetence/ |archivedate=2014-05-10 }}</ref>。该名女子不久后获释。有报道称，第一夫人提出一些由博科圣地支持者伪造的绑架报告，进一步激怒了示威者。数个在线请愿被发起，迫使尼日利亚政府针对绑架事件采取行动<ref>{{cite web|title=Nigerian schoolgirls|publisher=Walk free|url=http://www.walkfree.org/nigerian-schoolgirls/|accessdate=2016-08-21|archive-date=2014-05-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140506204908/http://www.walkfree.org/nigerian-schoolgirls/|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。4月30日，数百人在国会游行，要求采取打击绑匪的政府和军方行动<ref>{{cite news|newspaper=The Guardian|agency=Agence France-Presse|date=2014-04-30|title=Hundreds march: Nigeria Chibok schoolgirl kidnappings by Boko haram|url=http://www.theguardian.com/world/2014/apr/30/hundreds-march-nigeria-chibok-schoolgirl-kidnappings-boko-haram|accessdate=2016-08-21|archive-date=2016-07-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160723171725/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2014/apr/30/hundreds-march-nigeria-chibok-schoolgirl-kidnappings-boko-haram|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

{{le|尼日利亚穆斯林学生会|Muslim Students Society of Nigeria}}主席呼吁穆斯林绝食并祷告，以“在这种不稳定的时候寻求安拉的干预”<ref>{{cite web|title=Nigeria Muslims Fast for Abducted Girls|url=http://www.onislam.net/english/news/africa/472189-nigeria-muslims-fast-for-abducted-girls.html|publisher=On Islam|accessdate=2014-05-07|date=2014-05-06|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140507035640/http://www.onislam.net/english/news/africa/472189-nigeria-muslims-fast-for-abducted-girls.html|archivedate=2014-05-07}}</ref>。{{le|苏丹索科托|List of Sultans of Sokoto}}{{le|萨阿德·阿布巴卡尔|Sa'adu Abubakar}}也呼吁信众祈祷，并加大力度营救学生<ref>{{cite web|script-title=en:US Muslims Slam ‘Un-Islamic’ Boko Haram|url=http://www.onislam.net/english/news/americas/472177-us-muslims-slam-un-islamic-boko-haram.html|publisher=On Islam|accessdate=2014-05-07|date=2014-05-06|archive-date=2014-05-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140507033506/http://www.onislam.net/english/news/americas/472177-us-muslims-slam-un-islamic-boko-haram.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。5月9日，卡西姆·谢蒂马呼吁所有穆斯林和基督徒加入“祈祷绝食三天”的行列<ref>{{Cite news|title=Gov. Shettima declares 3-day fasting for abducted girls|work=The Nation|location=Lagos|accessdate=2014-05-09|date=2014-05-09|url=http://thenationonlineng.net/new/gov-shettima-declares-3-day-fasting-abducted-girls/|archive-date=2014-05-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140510194708/http://thenationonlineng.net/new/gov-shettima-declares-3-day-fasting-abducted-girls/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。同日，喀麦隆穆斯林呼吁同教弟兄如遇到有人表示可提供奇博克女孩嫁給他們時，應予拒絕<ref>{{cite news|title=Cameroon denies harbouring Chibok schoolgirls|work=Vanguard News|accessdate=2014-05-09|date=2014-05-09|url=http://www.vanguardngr.com/2014/05/cameroon-denies-harbouring-chibok-schoolgirls/|archive-date=2014-05-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140509081208/http://www.vanguardngr.com/2014/05/cameroon-denies-harbouring-chibok-schoolgirls/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。当天，{{le|沙特阿拉伯大穆夫提|Grand Mufti of Saudi Arabia}}{{le|谢赫·阿卜杜勒齐玆·谢赫|Sheikh Abdulaziz Al al-Sheikh}}与穆斯林世界其他宗教领袖称博科圣地的误导和意图抹黑了伊斯兰的名字。他表示，伊斯兰教反对绑架，而娶被绑女生是不被允许的<ref name="Grand Mufti`s reaction">{{cite news |last=Reuters |first=Thomson |title=Saudi Arabia's top cleric says Nigeria's Boko Haram smears Islam |url=http://www.globalpost.com/dispatch/news/thomson-reuters/140510/saudi-arabias-top-cleric-says-nigerias-boko-haram-smears-islam |accessdate=2014-05-11 |newspaper=GlobalPost |date=2014-05-10 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140511201606/http://www.globalpost.com/dispatch/news/thomson-reuters/140510/saudi-arabias-top-cleric-says-nigerias-boko-haram-smears-islam |archivedate=2014-05-11 }}</ref>。

绑架事件规模史无前例，让前美国驻尼日利亚大使约翰·坎贝尔（{{lang|en|John Campbell}}）惊叹博科圣地的实力“似乎越来越强。政府为公民提供安全保障的能力似乎在下降<ref name=USAToday>{{cite news|title=Terrorists kidnap more than 200 Nigerian girls|work=USA Today|first=Oren|last=Dorell|url=http://www.usatoday.com/story/news/world/2014/04/21/parents-234-girls-kidnapped-from-nigeria-school/7958307/|date=2014-04-21|accessdate=2014-04-23|archive-date=2014-04-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140422093712/http://www.usatoday.com/story/news/world/2014/04/21/parents-234-girls-kidnapped-from-nigeria-school/7958307/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。”而[[大西洋理事会|大西洋理事会]]非洲中心主任J·彼得·范（{{lang|en|J. Peter Pham}}）认为：“政府連提供一個清晰的數字也做不到，進一步令人覺得存在系统性的政府失效<ref name=USAToday/>。”《[[经济学人|经济学人]]》“给总统古德勒克·乔纳森打上不称职的标签”，表示“不能再靠乔纳森和尼军方保护尼日利亚人的安全”，并表示“尼日利亚政府处理绑架事件时最糟糕的地方在于似乎冷漠对待女孩家人的困境。乔纳森在事發超過兩個星期後始在公开場合就事件發表講話<ref name="thepunch20140509"/>。”乔纳森后来表示他初時保持沉默是因為不想透露過多細節，以免對营救女孩的行动造成不利<ref>{{cite news|last=Agba|first=George|url=http://allafrica.com/stories/201406301664.html|title=Nigeria: My Silence Over Chibok Girls is for Their Safety – Jonathan|publisher=allAfrica.com|date=2014-06-28|accessdate=2014-06-30|archive-date=2014-07-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140701164219/http://allafrica.com/stories/201406301664.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。他还花120万美元聘请[[公关|公关]]公司利维克提高他处理危机的公众形象<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/blogs-echochambers-28067547|title=Goodluck Jonathan: Silence isn't inaction|date=2014-06-07|accessdate=2014-07-18|archive-date=2014-07-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140719011928/http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/blogs-echochambers-28067547|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

7月23日和7月24日，世界各地举办了纪念绑架事件发生100天的守夜和抗议活动，包括尼日利亚、巴基斯坦、印度、孟加拉国、多哥、英国、美国、加拿大和葡萄牙<ref>{{cite web|title=100 days blog: #BringBackOurGirls vigils held around the world|url=http://www.aworldatschool.org/news/entry/100-days-blog-chibok-girls-vigils-around-world|publisher=A World At School|accessdate=2014-07-23|archive-date=2014-07-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140724105951/http://www.aworldatschool.org/news/entry/100-days-blog-chibok-girls-vigils-around-world|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

10月27日，[[人权观察组织|人权观察组织]]发表报告称：“他们的发言表明尼日利亚政府未能充分保护妇女和女同免受无数的虐待、在被俘后为她们提供有效的支持和心理健康和医疗、保障学校安全或调查并起诉为虐待案负责的人士<ref name=HRW>{{cite news|url=http://www.hrw.org/news/2014/10/27/nigeria-victims-abductions-tell-their-stories|title=Nigeria: Victims of Abductions Tell Their Stories: Horrific Abuses by Boko Haram, Lack of Government Protection|date=2014-10-27|website=HRW|accessdate=2014-10-27|archive-date=2014-10-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141027085104/http://www.hrw.org/news/2014/10/27/nigeria-victims-abductions-tell-their-stories|dead-url=no}}</ref>。”

截至2015年1月5日，带我们的女孩回来示威者在阿布贾统一喷泉的日常集会仍在继续，但警方努力压制群众<ref>{{cite news|last=Okello Kelo Sam|title=Abducted Nigerian girls still missing, a distracted world must remember|work=Los Angeles Times|accessdate=2015-01-08|date=2015-01-05|url=http://www.latimes.com/opinion/op-ed/la-oe-sam-bring-back-our-girls-20150108-story.html#navtype=outfit|archive-date=2015-01-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150108013107/http://www.latimes.com/opinion/op-ed/la-oe-sam-bring-back-our-girls-20150108-story.html#navtype=outfit|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Austine Elemue|title=Abuja’s Unity Fountain: Nigeria's Tahir Square?|work=The Abuja Inquirer|date=2015-01-07|accessdate=2015-01-08|url=http://www.theabujainquirer.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=1395:abuja-s-unity-fountain-nigeria-s-tahir-square&catid=90&Itemid=709|archive-date=2015-01-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150108213625/http://www.theabujainquirer.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=1395:abuja-s-unity-fountain-nigeria-s-tahir-square&catid=90&Itemid=709|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Hassan|first=Tina A|author2=Ogbu Amarachi Hannah|title=Nigeria: Unity Fountain - Abuja Landmark Turns Protest Venue|work=Media Trust - AllAfrica|accessdate=2015-01-08|date=2014-05-17|url=http://allafrica.com/stories/201405191617.html|archive-date=2015-01-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150108215206/http://allafrica.com/stories/201405191617.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Clement Ejiofor|title=#BringBackOurGirls Protesters Hold Demonstration in Abuja, Defy Police|website=naij.com|accessdate=2015-01-08|date=2014-05-11|url=http://www.naij.com/66115.html|archive-date=2015-01-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150108223015/http://www.naij.com/66115.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

2015年4月13日，数百名用红胶布封住嘴的抗议者沉默步行穿越阿布贾，纪念博科圣地绑架女孩一周年<ref>{{cite news|title=200 School Girls still untraceable after 1 Year of Kidnapping by Boko Haram|url=http://news.biharprabha.com/2015/04/200-school-girls-still-untraceable-after-1-year-of-kidnapping-by-boko-haram/|accessdate=2015-04-14|publisher=news.biharprabha.com|date=2015-04-14|archive-date=2015-07-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150712065239/http://news.biharprabha.com/2015/04/200-school-girls-still-untraceable-after-1-year-of-kidnapping-by-boko-haram/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

5月29日，尼日利亚总统[[穆罕默杜·布哈里|穆罕默杜·布哈里]]在他的就职全国演说中表示，“在救出奇博克女生以及其他被叛乱份子胁持为人质的无辜群众前，不能称已击败博科圣地。政府会儘其所能使他们活着獲救<ref>{{cite web |url=http://mbuhari.ng/full-text-of-the-inaugural-speech-of-president-muhammadu-buhari/ |title=Full text of the inaugural speech of President Muhammadu Buhari |last1= |first1= |last2= |first2= |date=2015-05-29 |website=mbuhari.ng |publisher= |accessdate=2015-06-19 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6ZNe6Q1aL?url=http://mbuhari.ng/full-text-of-the-inaugural-speech-of-president-muhammadu-buhari/ |archivedate=2015-06-18 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>。”

6月12日，布哈里总统宣誓就职过后仅两个星期，他携夫人{{le|艾莎·穆罕穆杜·布哈里|Aisha Buhari}}、副总统夫人多拉普·奥辛巴乔（{{lang|en|Dolapo Osinbajo}}）与被绑奇博克女生的部分母亲会面，而布哈里夫人希望会议能久一点<ref>{{cite news|url=http://dailypost.ng/2015/06/13/tears-as-aisha-buhari-mrs-osinbajo-meet-mothers-of-chibok/|work=Daily Post|title=Tears as Aisha Buhari, Mrs Osinbajo meet mothers of Chibok=2015-06-13|first=Ali|last=Adoyi|accessdate=2016-08-21|archive-date=2015-06-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150619000048/http://dailypost.ng/2015/06/13/tears-as-aisha-buhari-mrs-osinbajo-meet-mothers-of-chibok/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

10月1日，尼日利亚军方表示不会急于营救被绑的女生。阿布贾军事总部国防信息局代理主任拉贝·阿布巴卡尔上校（{{lang|en|Col. Rabe Abubakar}}）在上周四的新闻发布会上指出，尽管军方最为关心营救女孩，但行动需要足够的耐心和规划<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thenews.ng/metro/we-wont-rush-to-rescue-chibok-girls-%E2%94%80army|script-title=en:We won’t rush to rescue Chibok girls ─Army|last=|first=|date=2015-10-01|website=|publisher=thenews.ng|access-date=|work=Opemipo Adeniyi|accessdate=2015-10-02|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160223113045/https://thenews.ng/metro/we-wont-rush-to-rescue-chibok-girls-%E2%94%80army/|archivedate=2016-02-23}}</ref>。

12月，总统指出愿意无任何先决条件与博科圣地谈判释放奇博克女生<ref name=BBC31Dec>{{cite news|title=Nigerian president offers talks with Boko Haram over Chibok girls|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-africa-35203659|accessdate=2015-12-31|publisher=BBC News, Africa|date=2015-12-31|archive-date=2015-12-31|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151231025400/http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-africa-35203659|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

奇博克女生被绑的第600天，尼日利亚侨民安全论坛（{{lang|en|Nigeria Diaspora Security Forum}}）的英国尼日利亚专家呼吁尼日利亚联邦政府在总统穆罕穆杜·布哈里设立专门负责寻找女孩的特别工作组<ref>{{Cite web|title = Nigeria: Group Wants Special Taskforce On Boko Haram|url = http://allafrica.com/stories/201601270043.html|website = allAfrica.com|accessdate = 2016-01-31|archive-date = 2016-02-02|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160202091852/http://allafrica.com/stories/201601270043.html|dead-url = no}}</ref>。

